Introduction: Figma is a web-based design tool that lets you create professional interfaces for websites, apps, and other digital products. 

Usage instructions: (using Figma or any prototype tool) - Figma uses "workspaces" to organize projects. You can create personal workspaces or collaborate with others in shared workspaces.
Within a workspace, you'll create "frames" which are like individual pages for your designs. Figma offers various tools for creating design elements like shapes, lines, text boxes, and images. You can format these elements with colors, fonts, and effects.
It also has pre-built UI components (buttons, menus) to jumpstart your design process.

Any other relevant information: Figma offers a wealth of tutorials and resources on their website to help you get started and explore its features in more depth.
